message.content:
If someone wrote ten notes per day, then one notepad would have written one note every day for the past 5 days. 
After folding the paper and cutting along the lines, each note paper would have become 1/5 the size of the original. So, the total size of the stack of smaller note papers would be 1/5 the size of the original paper. 
If one note paper is 1/5 the size of the original paper, then the stack of smaller note papers would be 10/5 = 2 times the size of the original paper. 
Therefore, one notepad would have lasted for 5 days, as the stack of smaller note papers was twice as large as the original paper..
